to a totalitarian regime

33:53.422 --> 33:56.599
and a regime
that doesn't respect

33:56.730 --> 34:00.516
any international regulation
and convention.

34:08.655 --> 34:10.439
It was, like, I don't know,
00 in the morning

34:10.570 --> 34:12.485
or something like that.

34:12.615 --> 34:14.574
I got up groggy
and put on the first clothes

34:14.704 --> 34:16.271
that came to hand.

34:16.402 --> 34:18.186
Ended up
in the operations center

34:18.317 --> 34:20.667
in the State Department.

34:20.797 --> 34:23.365
It had speakers
on a long table,

34:23.496 --> 34:26.890
and each of those speakers
was connected

34:27.021 --> 34:29.328
to a phone inside the embassy,

34:29.458 --> 34:30.546
and we had
conversations back--

34:30.677 --> 34:32.548
"Can you hear anything?"

34:32.679 --> 34:36.204
And then one by one,
the phones suddenly went dead.

34:38.511 --> 34:42.428
That day was
when the first thoughts began

34:42.558 --> 34:46.388
to percolate about ways
to bring pressure on Iran.

34:46.519 --> 34:48.869
No one should underestimate
the resolve

34:48.999 --> 34:50.914
of the American government
and the American people

34:51.045 --> 34:53.091
in this matter.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.658
<i>Carter refused
to hand over the shah, </i>

34:55.789 --> 34:58.400
<i>instead imposing
a raft of sanctions... </i>

34:58.531 --> 35:00.359
I am ordering
that we discontinue

35:00.489 --> 35:04.058
the purchasing
of any oil from Iran.

35:04.189 --> 35:07.888
<i>...as part of an all-out
diplomatic offensive. </i>

35:08.018 --> 35:10.108
The message
the U.S. government

35:10.238 --> 35:12.110
wants to convey is that,
while you're trying

35:12.240 --> 35:15.417
to blackmail us by holding
our citizens hostage,

35:15.548 --> 35:17.071
we're going
to stand our ground.

35:17.202 --> 35:19.508
<i>But Iran's
revolutionary leader </i>

35:19.639 --> 35:21.597
<i>was not just hardnosed.</i>

35:21.728 --> 35:26.124
<i>He had changed the rules
of the game entirely. </i>

35:26.254 --> 35:28.909
Many people thought
he would be the figurehead,

35:29.039 --> 35:32.304
but he had no intention
of being a figurehead.

35:32.434 --> 35:35.045
He was more brutal
than all of them.

35:35.176 --> 35:37.483
As one official here
put it rather gloomily,

35:37.613 --> 35:40.399
you can't expect moderation
from a fanatic,

35:40.529 --> 35:42.923
so it's possible that,
for as long as the shah

35:43.053 --> 35:45.143
remains in this country,

35:45.273 --> 35:47.275
the Americans will remain
as hostages in Iran.

35:49.234 --> 35:52.541
I received a care package
from home,

35:52.672 --> 35:54.413
and it had some books in it--

35:54.543 --> 35:58.330
things like
"Brothers Karamazov,"

35:58.460 --> 36:02.725
"War and Peace,"
"Middlemarch."

36:02.856 --> 36:07.165
Average length about 900 pages.

36:07.295 --> 36:09.819
It was clear someone
was sending me a message

36:09.950 --> 36:11.865
that I was gonna have
plenty of time

36:11.995 --> 36:13.345
to read these books.

36:15.608 --> 36:17.436
<i>What was supposed to be
a quick stunt </i>

36:17.566 --> 36:21.135
<i>turned into weeks,
then months. </i>

36:21.266 --> 36:22.571
<i>Every day,
reporters and cameramen </i>

36:22.702 --> 36:23.964
<i>assemble at the gates.</i>

36:24.094 --> 36:26.401
<i>Thousands of words
are written, </i>

36:26.532 --> 36:28.925
<i>but facts
about the hostages are few. </i>

36:29.056 --> 36:31.798
The rise
of the hostage crisis

36:31.928 --> 36:34.844
coincided
with structural shifts

36:34.975 --> 36:38.108
in how the TV news business
was run,

36:38.239 --> 36:41.416
creating good guys
and bad guys

36:41.547 --> 36:43.592
and a melodramatic arc.

36:43.723 --> 36:47.248
<i>The Iran
America Held Hostage. </i>

36:47.379 --> 36:50.425
<i>ABC News even
launched a nightly program </i>

36:50.556 --> 36:52.122
<i>that made regulars
of hostage families. </i>

36:52.253 --> 36:54.734
<i>We know it today
as "Nightline." </i>

36:54.864 --> 36:56.649
Every morning,
Dotty Morefield

36:56.779 --> 36:58.912
writes to her husband Richard,
now a hostage.

36:59.042 --> 37:01.654
With us now
is Mrs. Morefield.

37:01.784 --> 37:04.874
Ted Koppel became Ted Koppel
as a result of all of this.

37:05.005 --> 37:07.268
<i>The media gave
each of the 53 Americans </i>

37:07.399 --> 37:10.445
<i>being held at the embassy
a face and a story. </i>

37:10.576 --> 37:11.838
21-year-old James Lopez

37:11.968 --> 37:13.970
is one of
the Iranian hostages.

37:14.101 --> 37:16.538
He knows that we're thinking
about him all the time.

37:16.669 --> 37:19.759
Weeping mothers
were a constant feature,

37:19.889 --> 37:22.544
and, you know,
the media celebrated

37:22.675 --> 37:24.546
what it called the rebirth
of American patriotism.

37:24.677 --> 37:27.549
What's on your mind
this Christmas Eve?

37:27.680 --> 37:29.203
The situation in Iran
right now--

37:29.334 --> 37:31.205
I wish the hostages
were back in here

37:31.336 --> 37:32.467
in this country
celebrating Christmas

37:32.598 --> 37:33.729
with their relatives.

37:36.123 --> 37:38.604
<i>In December,
the American news networks </i>

37:38.734 --> 37:40.214
<i>received a tape
from the Iranian students </i>

37:40.345 --> 37:42.695
<i>showing the hostages
participating </i>

37:42.825 --> 37:44.174
<i>in a bizarre
Christmas celebration. </i>

37:44.305 --> 37:46.307
One thing
you learn very quickly

37:46.438 --> 37:48.701
in a situation like this
is nothing's gonna make sense.

37:48.831 --> 37:50.877
All the Americans
here at the embassy

37:51.007 --> 37:52.095
have made
a special Christmas card

37:52.226 --> 37:54.054
to Imam Khomeini.

37:54.184 --> 37:57.536
A Christmas wish
especially for you.

37:57.666 --> 37:59.712
They ask us
to sing Christmas carols,

37:59.842 --> 38:01.714
which nobody wanted to do,
and the whole thing

38:01.844 --> 38:06.066
was so staged
and obviously a show.

38:07.285 --> 38:08.198
The students wanted to use it

38:08.329 --> 38:10.505
for their own purposes
to say,

38:10.636 --> 38:12.202
"Look how nice we are."

38:12.333 --> 38:13.856
<i>The sentimental
news coverage </i>

38:13.987 --> 38:16.294
<i>the hostage crisis
was receiving in America </i>

38:16.424 --> 38:18.731
<i>also gave the revolutionaries
an opening </i>

38:18.861 --> 38:20.950
<i>to once again
address the world. </i>

38:21.081 --> 38:23.866
I asked myself,
"What had the shah done?"

38:23.997 --> 38:26.216
My thinking
started to turn around.

38:26.347 --> 38:28.958
My eyes and mind were starting
to awake to the truth.

38:29.089 --> 38:31.178
The students,
they were very naive.

38:31.309 --> 38:33.789
They thought that Americans--
at least some Americans--

38:33.920 --> 38:35.617
would sympathize
with what they were doing.

38:35.748 --> 38:38.272
How much longer
can you go on doing this?

38:38.403 --> 38:40.840
We are ready to go on
until martyrdom.

38:40.970 --> 38:43.625
<i>
Hermitage, Pennsylvania--</i>

38:43.756 --> 38:46.106
<i>a flag for every day
the hostages have been held. </i>

38:46.236 --> 38:47.629
It would have been
a great moment

38:47.760 --> 38:49.805
to really, like,
explore the history

38:49.936 --> 38:52.460
of our dealings with Iran
and how high-handed

38:52.591 --> 38:54.114
and arrogant we were

38:54.244 --> 38:56.116
in our treatment
of the country,

38:56.246 --> 38:57.944
but we didn't seize
that opportunity,

38:58.074 --> 38:59.989
so we--a lot
of the coverage gave in

39:00.120 --> 39:02.775
to a kind of
nationalistic jingoism

39:02.905 --> 39:05.255
without any kind
of stocktaking of the policies

39:05.386 --> 39:06.953
that had gotten us
to this point.

39:07.083 --> 39:07.997
Down with Khomeini!
He's a murderer!

39:08.128 --> 39:09.608
He's a jerk!

39:09.738 --> 39:10.478
<i>
Yesterday in Houston,</i>

39:10.609 --> 39:12.654
<i>anti-Iranian demonstrators</i>

39:12.785 --> 39:14.874
<i>burned a flag in front
of the Iranian consulate. </i>

39:15.004 --> 39:16.876
<i>That demonstration
symbolizes what appears to be </i>

39:17.006 --> 39:18.834
<i>growing
anti-Iranian sentiment. </i>

39:18.965 --> 39:20.314
<i>Impatience
has turned to bitterness. </i>

39:20.445 --> 39:22.664
I don't see any reason
in this world

39:22.795 --> 39:25.101
for us to have to stand by
twiddling our thumbs.

39:25.232 --> 39:26.886
I feel we should show force.

39:27.016 --> 39:28.540
Let's take
some drastic action.

39:28.670 --> 39:30.585
I mean real drastic.

39:30.716 --> 39:32.065
<i>Pressure on President Carter
increased </i>

39:32.195 --> 39:33.632
<i>with each passing day</i>

39:33.762 --> 39:35.634
<i>the hostages
remained in captivity. </i>

39:35.764 --> 39:37.984
Do you have any plan
to resolve this?

39:38.114 --> 39:39.551
Do you plan to bring
any more pressures on Iran?

39:41.335 --> 39:44.077
We have done everything
we possibly could

39:44.207 --> 39:46.906
in the last four months
to try to preserve

39:47.036 --> 39:50.126
in every way the health
and the lives of those hostages

39:50.257 --> 39:53.652
and to work for their freedom.

39:53.782 --> 39:55.523
I don't know
when they'll be released.

39:56.872 --> 39:59.440
<i>By April of 1980,</i>

39:59.571 --> 40:03.705
<i>Carter felt he had no choice
but to respond with force. </i>

40:03.836 --> 40:06.404
<i>Diplomacy had failed,
and so he ordered </i>

40:06.534 --> 40:09.189
<i>a covert mission
to rescue the hostages. </i>

40:11.539 --> 40:13.541
<i>It would turn out to be
the greatest blunder </i>

40:13.672 --> 40:15.456
<i>of Carter's presidency.</i>

40:18.198 --> 40:19.678
<i>Good morning, everyone.</i>

40:19.808 --> 40:21.288
<i>I'm Tom Brokaw,
and we're starting </i>

40:21.419 --> 40:23.725
<i>at this early hour today
because of major developments </i>

40:23.856 --> 40:25.423
<i>in Iran.</i>

40:25.553 --> 40:27.729
<i>Eight American servicemen
were killed </i>

40:27.860 --> 40:29.862
<i>apparently in the crash
of a helicopter </i>

40:29.992 --> 40:32.995
<i>with a C-130 cargo plane
in Iran </i>

40:33.126 --> 40:34.910
<i>during a secret
United States mission </i>

40:35.041 --> 40:35.911
<i>to rescue the hostages.</i>

40:38.436 --> 40:40.089
My name's Jim Schaefer,

40:40.220 --> 40:43.441
major, United States
Marine Corps CH-53 pilot

40:43.571 --> 40:45.486
and a member
of the Iranian rescue attempt.

40:47.749 --> 40:50.752
It was just a loud thud.

40:50.883 --> 40:53.146
After that, I don't remember
much of anything.

40:53.276 --> 40:55.931
Waking up, and I know
the aircraft was on fire.

40:57.193 --> 40:58.760
So...

41:00.196 --> 41:01.937
This is the core
of the tragedy--

41:02.068 --> 41:03.722
the entire rotor assembly

41:03.852 --> 41:05.288
of one of
the American helicopters

41:05.419 --> 41:06.942
that were involved
in the rescue attempt.

41:12.295 --> 41:14.210
The molten aluminum
marked the intense heat

41:14.341 --> 41:16.343
of the blaze which followed,

41:16.474 --> 41:18.432
so intense that no American
could get near

41:18.563 --> 41:20.739
to drag clear the bodies
in the wreckage.

41:22.436 --> 41:25.831
It's just a horrible feeling
of failure,

41:25.961 --> 41:27.963
of letting our country down,
of letting the people,

41:28.094 --> 41:30.357
our troops down.

41:30.488 --> 41:33.534
It was really, really, really
a dark place.

41:38.844 --> 41:41.455
<i>News of the crash
ricocheted across Iran. </i>

41:41.586 --> 41:43.457
<i>
Word of the mission itself</i>

41:43.588 --> 41:45.981
<i>came as many thousands
of people were attending </i>

41:46.112 --> 41:48.723
<i>Friday prayers
at Tehran University. </i>

41:48.854 --> 41:50.072
<i>They heard it on their radios,</i>

41:50.203 --> 41:50.812
<i>and then there was
an announcement </i>

41:50.943 --> 41:52.031
<i>via the speaker.</i>

41:53.815 --> 41:54.990
<i>
That was a miracle.</i>

41:56.209 --> 42:00.126
That was divine support

42:00.256 --> 42:02.520
to Islamic revolution.

42:04.173 --> 42:06.088
I mean, the propaganda
was that

42:06.219 --> 42:07.525
<i>it was by the order of God.</i>

42:17.099 --> 42:20.799
I was able
to steal a newspaper.

42:20.929 --> 42:23.192
Not a lot of details,
but it was enough to know

42:23.323 --> 42:25.151
that there had been
a rescue attempt,

42:25.281 --> 42:28.328
that it had failed.

42:28.458 --> 42:30.330
After the raid,
we were scattered

42:30.460 --> 42:31.244
around the country.

42:33.942 --> 42:35.640
And I ended up
at Evin Prison,

42:35.770 --> 42:37.206
which is, like,

42:37.337 --> 42:38.773
one of the worst prisons
in the world,

42:38.904 --> 42:41.167
and I was way, way underground

42:41.297 --> 42:45.171
in a very small cell,

42:45.301 --> 42:47.260
and so I decide, okay,
I'm gonna take my own life.

42:47.390 --> 42:49.915
This is what I'm gonna do
because this is metal,

42:50.045 --> 42:52.178
and I played football
when I was younger and that,

42:52.308 --> 42:56.878
so I'm just gonna crash my head
into that door.

42:57.009 --> 42:58.445
And then I thought about it,
and I said,

42:58.576 --> 43:02.362
"Oh...that's real bright.

43:02.492 --> 43:03.755
You're not gonna die.

43:03.885 --> 43:04.669
You're just gonna
put yourself..."

43:06.366 --> 43:07.889
"You're gonna make
yourself irrelevant."

43:08.020 --> 43:11.980
I'd like to send a message
to the American people

43:12.111 --> 43:14.417
and the people of the world.

43:14.548 --> 43:17.464
I'd like to thank
all of them for the support

43:17.595 --> 43:19.901
that they have shown for us.

43:20.032 --> 43:21.468
There were sort of
really mixed emotions.

43:21.599 --> 43:24.776
Two things--one was,
of course, great sadness

43:24.906 --> 43:27.996
that brave people had died...

43:28.127 --> 43:30.564
in the attempt to get us out.

43:30.695 --> 43:33.219
The other, of course,
was great pride

43:33.349 --> 43:35.743
that, no,
we were not forgotten.

43:37.353 --> 43:40.879
Our rescue team knew
and I knew

43:41.009 --> 43:43.011
that the operation
was certain to be difficult,

43:43.142 --> 43:45.666
and it was certain
to be dangerous.

43:45.797 --> 43:48.843
To the families of those
who died and who were wounded,

43:48.974 --> 43:51.454
I want to express
the admiration I feel

43:51.585 --> 43:54.414
for the courage
of their loved ones

43:54.544 --> 43:55.807
and the sorrow
that I feel personally

43:55.937 --> 43:58.113
for their sacrifice.

43:58.244 --> 44:01.421
It was my decision to attempt
the rescue operation.

44:03.205 --> 44:06.426
The responsibility
is fully my own.

44:06.556 --> 44:09.081
To say, "Look,
this was my decision,

44:09.211 --> 44:13.215
and I take
full responsibility for it,"

44:13.346 --> 44:15.914
was a very hard thing
for him to do.

44:16.044 --> 44:18.960
It's a hard thing
for any president to do,

44:19.091 --> 44:20.962
and especially
a president who's involved

44:21.093 --> 44:23.704
in a very difficult
reelection campaign.

44:28.753 --> 44:30.624
<i>When Dorothea
Morefield heard the news, </i>

44:30.755 --> 44:32.321
<i>she did not know
what to make of it. </i>

44:32.452 --> 44:34.280
<i>Mrs. Morefield
kept switching channels </i>

44:34.410 --> 44:36.021
<i>looking for more information
on what happened. </i>

44:36.151 --> 44:37.631
They're Americans.

44:37.762 --> 44:38.806
They went in
to try and get them out,

44:38.937 --> 44:41.026
and I feel so badly.

44:41.156 --> 44:42.810
Do you think that it
will endanger Richard?

44:42.941 --> 44:44.682
I'm scared to death.

44:44.812 --> 44:48.163
It was yet one more image
of American humiliation

44:48.294 --> 44:51.384
to visit our television screens
every night.

44:51.514 --> 44:52.428
Are you concerned now
about the hostages?

44:52.559 --> 44:54.343
Very much so.

44:54.474 --> 44:56.302
I heard on the radio
this morning

44:56.432 --> 44:59.044
the mother of Rosen,
and she was crying bitterly

44:59.174 --> 45:01.263
and said that the president
was all wrong.

45:01.394 --> 45:06.051
After the abortive
rescue effort in Iran,

45:06.181 --> 45:07.835
one lady said, "My God,
can't we do anything right?"

45:13.101 --> 45:15.495
<i>Carter's failed mission
was red meat </i>

45:15.625 --> 45:17.366
<i>for televangelist
Jerry Falwell </i>

45:17.497 --> 45:19.020
<i>and his budding
political coalition </i>

45:19.151 --> 45:21.283
<i>of evangelicals.</i>

45:21.414 --> 45:23.155
<i>By this point,</i>

45:23.285 --> 45:25.374
<i>Falwell had given
this coalition a name-- </i>

45:25.505 --> 45:27.550
<i>the Moral Majority.</i>

45:27.681 --> 45:29.161
We are not preempted

45:29.291 --> 45:30.945
from going into
the political arena

45:31.076 --> 45:32.425
and fighting the battle there.

45:32.555 --> 45:34.514
As a matter of fact,
we're obligated to do it.

45:36.908 --> 45:39.127
<i>Mixing politics
with religion is a turnaround </i>

45:39.258 --> 45:41.303
<i>for this evangelist,
and he defends it vigorously. </i>

45:41.434 --> 45:43.001
If America's worth saving,

45:43.131 --> 45:45.090
then the preachers
need to fearlessly

45:45.220 --> 45:46.700
declare the issues

45:46.831 --> 45:49.094
no matter how unpopular
they may be.

45:51.183 --> 45:53.489
Evangelical
political involvement,

45:53.620 --> 45:57.319
it is ultimately a witness
of two things--

45:57.450 --> 46:02.368
our desire to serve others,
including those less fortunate,

46:02.498 --> 46:06.024
and our desire to share
our love for our God.

46:06.154 --> 46:08.026
Just pass
the envelopes out, please.

46:08.156 --> 46:09.592
Print your name and address.

46:09.723 --> 46:12.770
Make your checks payable
to Moral Majority.

46:12.900 --> 46:16.730
Make them as generous
as you can, please.

46:16.861 --> 46:19.994
By 1980, Jimmy Carter
is the enemy

46:20.125 --> 46:22.083
for a lot of these people.

46:22.214 --> 46:23.998
And I know people
have been telling me

46:24.129 --> 46:26.261
that Jimmy Carter's
doing his best,

46:26.392 --> 46:27.959
and that's our problem.

46:29.569 --> 46:31.310
<i>
To the nation's evangelicals,</i>

46:31.440 --> 46:33.878
<i>Ronald Reagan was a politician
who spoke their language. </i>

46:36.968 --> 46:41.146
Even though he was divorced
and he came out of Hollywood,

46:41.276 --> 46:44.627
there was great identification
with him rhetorically,

46:44.758 --> 46:46.499
and he welcomed them.

46:48.370 --> 46:51.547
He, at this time,
is standing firmly

46:51.678 --> 46:54.637
for those moral issues that we
are very concerned about.

46:54.768 --> 46:56.596
<i>And when it came
to the hostage crisis, </i>

46:56.726 --> 46:59.077
<i>Reagan's point of view
was simple. </i>

46:59.207 --> 47:02.515
I don't understand
why 52 Americans

47:02.645 --> 47:04.604
have been held hostage
for almost a year now.

47:06.519 --> 47:09.087
<i>Strong-arm Iran
and get the hostages back. </i>

47:09.217 --> 47:10.784
It was absolutely
at the center

47:10.915 --> 47:12.786
of his political
and moral imagination

47:12.917 --> 47:15.049
that America rescued
its hostages.

47:15.180 --> 47:16.616
We've endured
this humiliation

47:16.746 --> 47:18.618
for just lacking one week
of a year now.

47:18.748 --> 47:20.489
So, you know,
if you wanted to vote

47:20.620 --> 47:22.056
for a hawk, you know,
you might as well

47:22.187 --> 47:23.579
vote for the guy
who promised you

47:23.710 --> 47:25.277
a 30% tax cut
over the guy who tells you

47:25.407 --> 47:26.191
you're gonna have
to make do with less.

47:28.193 --> 47:31.761
This country
needs a new administration

47:31.892 --> 47:35.243
with a renewed dedication
to the dream of an America,

47:35.374 --> 47:38.029
an administration that will
give that dream new life.

47:38.159 --> 47:42.468
We will
make America great again.

47:44.862 --> 47:49.388
The greatness of America
as a city set upon a hill

47:49.518 --> 47:52.391
that would be a moral example
to the rest of the world

47:52.521 --> 47:55.611
that the rest of the world
would want to emulate--

47:55.742 --> 47:58.571
particularly for evangelicals,

47:58.701 --> 48:02.183
that was a very powerful view
of America.

48:02.314 --> 48:06.666
Inside this little packet
is an Old Glory flag pin.

48:06.796 --> 48:08.581
Now, if you're ashamed
of America, don't wear it.

48:08.711 --> 48:11.192
Go on over and join Khomeini.

48:11.323 --> 48:13.412
You might say it was
a marriage made in heaven.

48:13.542 --> 48:15.109
Heyo.

48:15.240 --> 48:17.764
Religious America
is awakening

48:17.895 --> 48:21.115
perhaps just in time
for our country's sake.

48:26.642 --> 48:28.296
Just to bring you up to date
on the presidential race,

48:28.427 --> 48:30.385
it is looking very good
for Ronald Reagan at this time.

48:30.516 --> 48:32.300
It's a tremendous landslide.

48:32.431 --> 48:35.173
Unanticipated, unexpected.

48:35.303 --> 48:37.523
The hostage thing came in
in a sneaky way,

48:37.653 --> 48:39.133
and it just collapsed
for Carter.

48:39.264 --> 48:41.266
And all of this arrived
on top of inflation,

48:41.396 --> 48:42.876
unemployment, and so on--

48:43.007 --> 48:44.138
all of the problems
we know about.

48:44.269 --> 48:47.794
And roughly 25%

48:47.925 --> 48:51.363
of all voters told pollsters

48:51.493 --> 48:53.452
they were regular viewers
of Christian television.

48:55.236 --> 48:57.238
<i>Carter only won six states.</i>

48:57.369 --> 48:59.762
<i>It was a wipeout.</i>

49:05.812 --> 49:09.163
I promised you four years ago

49:09.294 --> 49:12.297
that I would never lie to you,

49:12.427 --> 49:14.734
so I can't stand here tonight
and say it doesn't hurt.

49:22.394 --> 49:24.439
In all the days and months
when I have served you

49:24.570 --> 49:26.267
and served this country,

49:26.398 --> 49:28.791
you've readily given me
your shoulders,

49:28.922 --> 49:31.794
your faith, and your prayers.

49:31.925 --> 49:34.667
No man could ask any more
of his friends.

49:36.277 --> 49:39.585
He wasn't a showman,

49:39.715 --> 49:43.241
but he really
gave the American people

49:43.371 --> 49:47.462
full value for their election.

49:47.593 --> 49:50.248
Jimmy Carter actually asked
the American people to think

49:50.378 --> 49:54.339
and to take
their job seriously,

49:54.469 --> 49:58.647
and a lot of people
really do appreciate that

49:58.778 --> 50:00.998
and understand it,

50:01.128 --> 50:03.043
and I think a lot
of other people really don't.

50:05.437 --> 50:06.307
Do the Carter people feel
that they could have

50:06.438 --> 50:08.353
done it differently?

50:08.483 --> 50:10.616
Any one single thing
they should have done better.

50:10.746 --> 50:14.576
John, they point constantly
to this hostage situation.

50:14.707 --> 50:17.231
<i>Even after his loss,
Carter continued </i>

50:17.362 --> 50:19.929
<i>to negotiate for the hostages,</i>

50:20.060 --> 50:23.237
<i>but Iran continued
to deny him a resolution </i>

50:23.368 --> 50:24.673
<i>right up until
the very last minute </i>

50:24.804 --> 50:25.805
<i>of his presidency.</i>

50:30.984 --> 50:32.942
<i>
Live from Washington D.C.,</i>

50:33.073 --> 50:35.162
<i>NBC News
covers the inauguration </i>

50:35.293 --> 50:36.642
<i>of Ronald Reagan.</i>

50:43.823 --> 50:46.652
Well, the night before,
oh, about00,

50:46.782 --> 50:48.306
00 at night,
they came in,

50:48.436 --> 50:49.698
and they said,
"We're letting you go."

50:55.487 --> 50:58.490
That day, I was
in the Oval Office.

50:58.620 --> 51:00.492
Both planes
at the end of the runway.

51:00.622 --> 51:02.929
And then we started
to get notices

51:03.060 --> 51:05.236
the hostages were moving.

51:05.366 --> 51:06.541
We'll let you know
when to take off.

51:06.672 --> 51:08.674
What is--that's close.

51:08.804 --> 51:11.894
We were sitting in a room.

51:12.025 --> 51:14.419
These guys exploded
in there saying,

51:14.549 --> 51:16.421
"Get your stuff.
Let's go."

51:16.551 --> 51:18.249
They took off our blindfolds,
and we walked

51:18.379 --> 51:19.554
towards the airplane.

51:21.469 --> 51:22.949
We do think
that the hostages

51:23.080 --> 51:26.039
will be leaving Tehran Airport
before long.

51:26.170 --> 51:28.694
The idea that the release
would come

51:28.824 --> 51:31.871
within minutes of Ronald Reagan
raising his right hand

51:32.001 --> 51:36.571
is to be believed
in fiction only.

51:36.702 --> 51:39.661
Reagan arrived on the steps
of the White House,

51:39.792 --> 51:43.404
and Carter went down,
got in the car with him.

51:43.535 --> 51:46.364
So at that point
I left and went down

51:46.494 --> 51:48.627
to the operations center
in the basement,

51:48.757 --> 51:51.238
and I followed the situation.

51:56.243 --> 51:58.376
Were people talking about
the hostages down there?

51:58.506 --> 52:00.943
Someone said
that they were airborne.

52:01.074 --> 52:02.293
Mr. President,
are the hostages out?

52:02.423 --> 52:03.990
Can't say yet.

52:04.121 --> 52:05.818
Not yet.
They've cheated him.

52:05.948 --> 52:07.733
They've cheated him
right down to the end.

52:10.039 --> 52:13.521
Reverend Falwell,
what does this day mean to you?

52:13.652 --> 52:16.307
I think this is a day with
a real supernatural meaning.

52:16.437 --> 52:19.701
I--the hostages'
potential release,

52:19.832 --> 52:22.095
a new president,
a new administration.

52:22.226 --> 52:23.575
Perhaps God
may give to this country

52:23.705 --> 52:24.793
a new beginning.

52:28.971 --> 52:31.409
Raise your right hand
and repeat after me.

52:31.539 --> 52:33.933
I, Ronald Reagan,
do solemnly swear...

52:34.063 --> 52:36.631
I, Ronald Reagan, do
solemnly swear...

52:36.762 --> 52:38.938
...that I will faithfully
execute the office

52:39.068 --> 52:40.940
of president
of the United States.

52:41.070 --> 52:42.768
...that I will
faithfully execute

52:42.898 --> 52:44.944
the office of president
of the United States.

52:45.074 --> 52:48.774
- So help you God.
- So help me God.

52:48.904 --> 52:51.429
<i>Minutes after Reagan
raised his right hand, </i>

52:51.559 --> 52:52.647
<i>the plane
carrying the hostages </i>

52:52.778 --> 52:55.433
<i>left the ground in Tehran.</i>

52:58.000 --> 53:00.873
The stands are filled.

53:01.003 --> 53:02.701
The weather is easy.

53:02.831 --> 53:05.617
- The hostages are free.
- Hooray!

53:05.747 --> 53:08.924
Looks as though
President Reagan

53:09.055 --> 53:11.840
has been spared the requirement
of dealing on the hostages.

53:11.971 --> 53:13.451
<i>Spared for now.</i>

53:15.627 --> 53:20.719
Reagan was allowed
to bask in this victory

53:20.849 --> 53:23.461
that the hostages had returned
safe and sound by and large.

53:25.767 --> 53:28.770
<i>And the cheering
begins even before we see </i>

53:28.901 --> 53:30.337
<i>the first
of the returning Americans. </i>

53:32.644 --> 53:35.124
<i>This is one of the first
national experiences </i>

53:35.255 --> 53:38.911
<i>that America's had in years
in which everybody feels good. </i>

53:39.041 --> 53:40.521
How are you?
Nice to see you.

53:40.652 --> 53:41.435
I didn't know
what I was coming back to.

53:41.566 --> 53:44.482
I thought, "Wow, boy,

53:44.612 --> 53:46.527
are we gonna be
in some trouble."

53:46.658 --> 53:52.011
And, of course, we were
just treated like gold.

53:52.141 --> 53:54.405
John Limbert believes
that wholesale condemnation

53:54.535 --> 53:56.537
of the Iranian people
is wrong.

53:56.668 --> 53:58.887
I do say they're people
of talent,

53:59.018 --> 54:02.239
ability, great kindness,
great hospitality.

54:02.369 --> 54:04.284
That's what I thought before.
I still think so.

54:06.634 --> 54:08.375
<i>Seven days
after taking office... </i>

54:11.204 --> 54:13.293
<i>...Reagan welcomed
the hostages home </i>

54:13.424 --> 54:16.296
<i>with a patriotic celebration
fit for American heroes. </i>

54:20.648 --> 54:24.696
You come home to a people
who for 444 days

54:24.826 --> 54:27.481
suffered the pain
of your imprisonment,

54:27.612 --> 54:29.918
prayed for your safety,
and most importantly

54:30.049 --> 54:32.225
shared your determination

54:32.356 --> 54:34.053
that the spirit
of free men and women

54:34.183 --> 54:36.751
is not a fit subject
for barter.

54:40.059 --> 54:42.235
Now, I'll not be
so foolish as to say,

54:42.366 --> 54:43.584
"Forget what
you've been through."

54:43.715 --> 54:46.065
You never will.

54:46.195 --> 54:48.633
But turn the page
and look ahead.

54:50.287 --> 54:52.854
To me,
that's Reaganism to a T--

54:52.985 --> 54:54.987
the idea that history

54:55.117 --> 54:57.250
is not something
to learn from,

54:57.381 --> 55:00.558
that we don't
transcend our traumas

55:00.688 --> 55:02.908
by facing them unflinchingly,

55:03.038 --> 55:07.042
but that we kind of create
this sort of fantasy America

55:07.173 --> 55:09.218
in which
there are no problems,

55:09.349 --> 55:11.003
except for problems
that are kind of visited

55:11.133 --> 55:13.266
upon America from,
you know, forces

55:13.397 --> 55:14.528
that are not really
American at all.

55:15.312 --> 55:17.662
Let terrorists be aware

55:17.792 --> 55:19.968
that when the rules
of international behavior

55:20.099 --> 55:22.971
are violated,
our policy will be one

55:23.102 --> 55:26.584
of swift
and effective retribution.

55:28.368 --> 55:32.285
And then five years later,
it comes up again.

55:32.416 --> 55:34.374
<i>And that's how we get back
to Iran-Contra... </i>

55:36.463 --> 55:38.160
<i>...when Ronald Reagan
found himself </i>

55:38.291 --> 55:40.511
<i>enveloped in a hostage crisis
of his own. </i>

55:42.251 --> 55:43.818
<i>Reagan had reached
the White House </i>

55:43.949 --> 55:45.690
<i>in part by attacking
his opponent's approach </i>

55:45.820 --> 55:48.301
<i>to the same exact problem.</i>

55:48.432 --> 55:50.608
<i>In doing so,
the new president </i>

55:50.738 --> 55:52.740
<i>had painted himself
into a corner, </i>

55:52.871 --> 55:55.656
<i>a hostage of his own making.</i>

55:55.787 --> 55:58.267
And maybe
that's the Greek tragedy--

55:58.398 --> 56:01.706
that you cannot
escape your fate.

56:01.836 --> 56:03.708
<i>The hearing
will please come to order. </i>
